Develop an HTML page with three sections that are displayed side-by-side, each containing different colors. Modify the code below to create the intended display.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <style>
        .section {
            height: 100%;
            width: 33.333%;
            display: inline-block;
        }
        .red { background-color: red; }
        .green { background-color: green; }
        .blue { background-color: blue; }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="section red"></div>
    <div class="section green"></div>
    <div class="section blue"></div>
</body>
</html>
```

Fix the provided code to ensure that the sections fill the entire width and height of the screen and are displayed side-by-side without any gaps between them. Make sure the HTML file is valid with proper use of tags and syntax.

